<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1495,2008]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,152,258]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="9" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,1495,1521]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small 
<taxonomicName box="[408,561,1496,1521]" class="Entognatha" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Lepidocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[408,561,1496,1521]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="47">Lepidocyrtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[580,646,1496,1522]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
of maximum body length) with mesothorax not projecting over the head and body color very variable, from white to purple and with various color patterns taxonomically considered subspecies (
<figureCitation box="[351,489,1576,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1391,1415]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,277,1350]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[188,1398,277,1365]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 25. Lepidocyrtus lusitanicus - complex: 21, L. lusitanicus lusitanicus; 22, L. lusitanicus coloratus; 23, L. lusitanicus nigrus; 24, L. lusitanicus piezoensis; 25, L. lusitanicus form A." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184645/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="47">
Figs 
<number box="[411,489,1576,1602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="23.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="21.0">21–25</number>
</figureCitation>
). The new form (A) possess characteristic color pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1251,1576,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 25" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1391,1415]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,277,1350]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[188,1398,277,1365]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 25. Lepidocyrtus lusitanicus - complex: 21, L. lusitanicus lusitanicus; 22, L. lusitanicus coloratus; 23, L. lusitanicus nigrus; 24, L. lusitanicus piezoensis; 25, L. lusitanicus form A." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184645/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[1217,1251,1576,1602]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
): diffuse purple pigment in ant. II–IV, head, th. II–abd. II and coxae, and with the th. II anterior margin conspicuously darker pigmented. Antennae, legs and dorsal side of manubrium not scaled. Ant. IV with simple nonretractile apical bulb (
<figureCitation box="[219,307,1696,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 27" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1594,1618]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,301,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[161,1426,287,1566]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 27. Lepidocyrtus lusitanicus: 26, apical antennal bulb; 27, abd. IV chaetotaxy, broad circles –– broad ciliated macrochaetae, small circles –– thin ciliated macrochaetae, white circle –– pseudopore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184646/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[274,307,1696,1722]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
). Labium chaetotaxy [M 
<number box="[597,605,1712,1726]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
] M 
<number box="[648,656,1712,1726]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="2.0">2</number>
R*EL 
<number box="[726,734,1712,1726]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
L 
<number box="[752,760,1712,1726]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="2.0">2</number>
(M 
<date box="[804,870,1696,1726]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47">
<number box="[804,812,1712,1726]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
may
</date>
be present or absent, R half in length than other setae). Labrum 
<number box="[336,351,1738,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[360,406,1738,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="554.0">554</number>
; prelabral setae ciliated, labral setae smooth; inverted U-shaped labral apical intrusion. Ventral cephalic groove with 
<number box="[516,530,1778,1804]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number box="[548,562,1778,1804]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
ciliated setae. Head with a maximum of 
<number box="[1083,1097,1778,1804]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="7.0">7</number>
+ 
<number box="[1114,1128,1778,1804]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="7.0">7</number>
macrochaetae in row A. Intraocular chaetotaxy with ciliated setae s, t, r, q, p, without scales. Dorsal macrochaetae formula R0R 
<number box="[198,206,1875,1889]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
R 
<number box="[226,234,1875,1889]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="2.0">2</number>
STSo/ 
<number box="[311,339,1858,1884]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="10.0">10</number>
/0301+ 
<number box="[424,437,1858,1884]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
, with supplementary macrochaetae R 
<number box="[881,888,1875,1889]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
s between R0 and R 
<number box="[1117,1125,1875,1889]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
. Abd. II setae a 
<number box="[1318,1334,1858,1884]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="2.0">2</number>
, m 
<number box="[1372,1385,1858,1884]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
and m 
<number box="[176,189,1902,1928]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="3.0">3</number>
e ciliated macrochaetae; seta a 
<number box="[545,559,1902,1928]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="2.0">2</number>
p absent. Abd. IV trichobothrium T 
<number box="[977,991,1902,1928]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="2.0">2</number>
without accesory seta s; seta D 
<number box="[1362,1372,1902,1928]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
p ciliated and double in length than other setae of the trichobotrial complex; setae E 
<number box="[1146,1157,1942,1968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
, De 
<number box="[1214,1224,1942,1968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
and E 
<number box="[1309,1323,1942,1968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="4.0">4</number>
p smooth mesochaetae; setae Fe 
<number box="[410,424,1982,2008]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="4.0">4</number>
ciliated macrochaeta or smooth mesochaeta depending on the specimens (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1378,1982,2008]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 27" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1594,1618]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,301,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[161,1426,287,1566]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 27. Lepidocyrtus lusitanicus: 26, apical antennal bulb; 27, abd. IV chaetotaxy, broad circles –– broad ciliated macrochaetae, small circles –– thin ciliated macrochaetae, white circle –– pseudopore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/184646/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="47">
Fig. 
<number box="[1345,1378,1982,2008]" pageId="9" pageNumber="47" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
). All setae associated with the trichobothria on abd. II–IV are acuminate and strongly ciliate. V-shaped trochanteral organ formed by 
<number box="[357,401,192,218]" pageId="10" pageNumber="48" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8</number>
smooth setae. Inner edge of the unguis with basal pair teeth and one or two odd teeth; unguiculus with outer edge serrate or smooth. Manubrial plate with 
<number box="[947,961,232,258]" pageId="10" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
internal setae and 
<number box="[1182,1225,232,258]" pageId="10" pageNumber="48" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
external setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
